FROSTED ICING settled near the back three deep in the early going, angled out six wide for the stretch drive to be have clear run and was not involved late running evenly to the finish. JIBARO took command from the start, set the fractions comfortably on the front end, was collared running on the rail at the three sixteenths marker by runners and stopped in the final sixteenth of a mile. SMALL TALK prompted the pace outside in the two path keeping a close eye on the pacesetter throughout the turn, was in the hunt turning for home between runners two deep, gave way at the furlong marker and tired in deep stretch.
